      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(diagnostics): rotate cache trace and payload JSONL logs",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add opt-in archive rotation to the queued JSONL writer while preserving cap-and-drop behavior for existing maxFileBytes-only callers.\n- Bound diagnostic JSONL sinks by default: cache trace rotates at 50 MB with 3 archives; Anthropic provider payload logs rotate at 100 MB with 5 archives.\n- Add config/env wiring, generated schema metadata, docs, and changelog entries for the new caps and archive retention controls.\n\n## Impact\nThis is an operational safety fix. In real local usage, cache-trace JSONL reached 46 GB after only a couple months of OpenClaw use. Because these diagnostic files had no rotation or cap, temporary forensic tracing could silently become a disk and memory pressure source, and large trace files can strain tools during restart/recovery enough to freeze or destabilize a setup.\n\n## Testing\n- pnpm exec vitest run src/agents/queued-file-writer.test.ts src/agents/cache-trace.test.ts src/agents/anthropic-payload-log.test.ts src/config/logging-max-file-bytes.test.ts src/infra/dotenv.test.ts\n- pnpm exec vitest run src/config/schema.help.quality.test.ts src/config/schema.base.generated.test.ts src/config/config.schema-regressions.test.ts\n- pnpm config:schema:check\n- pnpm config:docs:check\n- pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 <changed TS files>\n- env OPENCLAW_OXLINT_SKIP_PREPARE=1 node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig tsconfig.oxlint.core.json <changed TS files>\n- pnpm tsgo:core:test\n\nFixes #75380.\nRelated: #41676, #74801, #73655, #57031.",
